<div id="review_181570516" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/181570516" />
    <a title="Lawanna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5714812-lawanna"><img alt="Lawanna" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1310518422p2/5714812.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/181570516?book_show_action=true">Jul 03, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lawanna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lawanna" href="/user/show/5714812-lawanna">Lawanna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer181570516" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11413623374952480388">This book was nothing like my usual first choice. I really liked the story though. I have talked about it to so many people since I first opened it, that I have a list of people wanting to borrow my book. <br/><br/>The author did a nice job of capturing the emotionalism of the the early sixties in the south. I grew up in Massachussetts, and have lived in North Carolina for seventeen years now. I wasn&apos;t born until eleven years after the story took place. This book was the first exposure I have had to what </span>
  <span id="freeText11413623374952480388" style="display:none">This book was nothing like my usual first choice. I really liked the story though. I have talked about it to so many people since I first opened it, that I have a list of people wanting to borrow my book. <br /><br />The author did a nice job of capturing the emotionalism of the the early sixties in the south. I grew up in Massachussetts, and have lived in North Carolina for seventeen years now. I wasn't born until eleven years after the story took place. This book was the first exposure I have had to what segregation that took place here. There was so much emotion, hatred, anger and confusion that it is easy to understand how a young girl could get pulled in to a cause so much bigger than herself. <br /><br />Jeri, the main character was a naive young girl that at times seems like a spoiled brat. She was persistent though and you couldn't help but to cross your fingers and hope her energy was not misplaced. <br /><br />The only thing that caused me to scratch my head was not knowing if this book was fiction, biography or even autobiography. The authors name differs from the name used for the main character,however she shares a history with her. There was no disclaimer found in the fvront of the book as all other fictional stories have. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11413623374952480388" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


