<div id="review_203590319" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/203590319" />
    <a title="Mill City Press" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2665283-mill-city-press"><img alt="Mill City Press" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1437057038p2/2665283.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/203590319?book_show_action=true">Aug 30, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mill City Press" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mill City Press" href="/user/show/2665283-mill-city-press">Mill City Press</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2665283-mill-city-press?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer203590319" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer643037214907120978">Bridge of the Single Hair is about a young woman&apos;s journey during the Freedom Rides and her subsequent incarceration for civil disobedience. She meets a young black man during her term in the Mississippi state penitentiary. She tries to help him, endangering her life and the lives of others. <br/><br/>The historical accuracy of Bridge of the Single Hair is impressive, and helps create a poignant and thought-provoking story about race and justice in the 1960s Deep South. The prose is simple, engaging, and </span>
  <span id="freeText643037214907120978" style="display:none">Bridge of the Single Hair is about a young woman's journey during the Freedom Rides and her subsequent incarceration for civil disobedience. She meets a young black man during her term in the Mississippi state penitentiary. She tries to help him, endangering her life and the lives of others. <br /><br />The historical accuracy of Bridge of the Single Hair is impressive, and helps create a poignant and thought-provoking story about race and justice in the 1960s Deep South. The prose is simple, engaging, and descriptive. This coming-of-age story about race, justice, and civil rights will interest a wide variety of readers with its fascinating subject matter and smooth pace. </span>
  <a data-text-id="643037214907120978" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


